# INTERVIEW REVISION SECTION

---

## 7.1 Last-Minute Revision Notes (The One-Pager)

### Layers at a Glance
```
OSI: Application → Presentation → Session → Transport → Network → Data Link → Physical
TCP/IP: Application → Transport → Internet → Network Access
PDU:   Data → Segment → Packet → Frame → Bits
```

### Critical Protocols by Layer

| Layer | Protocols | Port |
|-------|-----------|------|
| Application | HTTP(80), HTTPS(443), DNS(53), FTP(21/20), SSH(22), SMTP(25), DHCP(67/68), Telnet(23) | See left |
| Transport | TCP (reliable, connection-oriented), UDP (fast, connectionless) | — |
| Network | IP, ICMP, ARP, OSPF, RIP, BGP | — |
| Data Link | Ethernet, Wi-Fi, PPP | — |
| Physical | Cables, signals, encoding | — |

### Must-Know Processes
```
TCP 3-way handshake: SYN → SYN+ACK → ACK
TCP 4-way close:     FIN → ACK → FIN → ACK (+ TIME_WAIT 2×MSL)
DHCP DORA:           Discover → Offer → Request → Acknowledge
DNS hierarchy:        Browser cache → OS → Router → ISP → Root → TLD → Authoritative
ARP:                 Broadcast "Who has IP?" → Unicast reply "I'm at MAC"
```

### Key Differences (Ultra-Short)
```
TCP = reliable, slow, connection | UDP = fast, unreliable, connectionless
Hub = L1, broadcast all | Switch = L2, MAC-based | Router = L3, IP-based
IPv4 = 32-bit, 4.3B | IPv6 = 128-bit, no NAT needed
HTTP = port 80, plaintext | HTTPS = port 443, TLS encrypted
Forward proxy = hides client | Reverse proxy = hides server
Flow control = protect receiver | Congestion control = protect network
GBN = retransmit all from error | SR = retransmit only lost frame
Static routing = manual | Dynamic = RIP/OSPF/BGP
Circuit switching = dedicated path | Packet switching = shared, dynamic
```

---

## 7.2 Important Formulas

| Formula | Context |
|---------|---------|
| `Delay = Propagation + Transmission + Processing + Queuing` | Total delay |
| `Propagation delay = Distance / Speed` | Signal travel time |
| `Transmission delay = Packet size / Bandwidth` | Time to push bits on wire |
| `Throughput ≤ Bandwidth` | Always true |
| `Nyquist: C = 2B log₂(L)` | Max rate, noiseless channel |
| `Shannon: C = B log₂(1 + SNR)` | Max rate, noisy channel |
| `Efficiency (S&W) = 1 / (1 + 2a)` | a = prop. delay / tx delay |
| `Efficiency (Sliding Window) = W / (1 + 2a)` | W = window size, if W ≤ 1+2a |
| `Full mesh links = n(n-1)/2` | n = number of nodes |
| `Subnets = 2^(borrowed bits)` | Subnetting |
| `Hosts = 2^(host bits) - 2` | Usable hosts per subnet |
| `Block size = 256 - mask value` | Subnet block calculation |
| `GBN sender window ≤ 2^n - 1` | n = sequence number bits |
| `SR sender window ≤ 2^(n-1)` | n = sequence number bits |
| `Hamming parity bits: 2^r ≥ m + r + 1` | m = data bits |
| `Pure ALOHA efficiency = 1/(2e) ≈ 18.4%` | Maximum throughput |
| `Slotted ALOHA efficiency = 1/e ≈ 36.8%` | Maximum throughput |

