## 7.3 Memory Tricks & Mnemonics

### OSI Layers (Top → Bottom)
**"All People Seem To Need Data Processing"**
- Application, Presentation, Session, Transport, Network, Data Link, Physical

### OSI Layers (Bottom → Top)
**"Please Do Not Throw Sausage Pizza Away"**
- Physical, Data Link, Network, Transport, Session, Presentation, Application

### IP Classes
**"All Boys Create Deadly Enemies"**
- Class A (1-126), B (128-191), C (192-223), D (224-239), E (240-255)

### TCP Flags
**"Unskilled Attackers Pester Real Security Folks"**
- URG, ACK, PSH, RST, SYN, FIN

### DHCP Process
**"DORA the Explorer"**
- Discover, Offer, Request, Acknowledge

### Port Numbers (Common)
```
"FTP loves SSH" → 21, 22
"Telnet then SMTP" → 23, 25
"DNS is key" → 53
"HTTP is 80, HTTPS is 443" → remember by adding 363
"DHCP: Server 67, Client 68" → sequential pair
```

### Private IP Ranges
```
10.x.x.x           → "10 is TEN" (Class A, one range)
172.16-31.x.x       → "172 middle" (Class B, 16 ranges)
192.168.x.x         → "Home sweet 192.168" (Class C, most common)
```

### Subnetting Power of 2
```
2^1=2, 2^2=4, 2^3=8, 2^4=16, 2^5=32, 2^6=64, 2^7=128, 2^8=256
Corresponding CIDR masks (/24→/32):
/25=128, /26=192, /27=224, /28=240, /29=248, /30=252, /31=254, /32=255
```

