## 7.5 1-Day Revision Strategy

**For interview tomorrow (8-hour intensive):**

| Time | Activity |
|------|----------|
| 9:00-10:00 | Read Part 1: Fundamentals + OSI/TCP-IP (skim, focus on tables) |
| 10:00-11:30 | Read Part 2: Data Link + Network Layer (focus on subnetting examples) |
| 11:30-12:30 | Read Part 3: Transport + Application (TCP handshake, DNS, HTTP) |
| 12:30-1:00 | Lunch break |
| 1:00-2:00 | Read Part 4: Security + Modern Networking (TLS, CDN, LB) |
| 2:00-3:30 | Study ALL comparison tables in Part 5 |
| 3:30-5:00 | Practice interview questions (Part 5) — say answers out loud |
| 5:00-5:30 | Review rapid-fire questions |
| 5:30-6:00 | Review this revision section — formulas, mnemonics, forgotten concepts |

**Key rule:** Don't try to learn new things. Focus on recalling what you already know.

