## 30-Day Intensive CN Roadmap

> For students with 2-3 hours/day who need quick placement prep.

| Day | Topic | Key Activities |
|-----|-------|---------------|
| 1 | Network basics | Types, topologies, transmission modes |
| 2 | Performance metrics | Bandwidth, latency, throughput, switching types |
| 3 | OSI Model (L1-L4) | Physical, Data Link, Network, Transport layers |
| 4 | OSI Model (L5-L7) + TCP/IP | Session, Presentation, Application + TCP/IP comparison |
| 5 | Physical Layer | Signals, media, encoding, multiplexing |
| 6 | Data Link: Framing + Error | Framing, parity, CRC calculation practice |
| 7 | Data Link: Hamming Code | Hamming code calculation + practice problems |
| 8 | Flow Control: Stop-and-Wait | Protocol mechanics, efficiency calculation |
| 9 | Flow Control: GBN + SR | Window sizes, retransmission, comparison |
| 10 | MAC + Ethernet + Switching | MAC protocols, CSMA/CD, switch operation |
| 11 | VLANs + Review DLL | VLAN concepts, revise all Data Link topics |
| 12 | IPv4 Addressing | Classes, special addresses, private ranges |
| 13 | Subnetting (Basic) | Simple subnetting with worked examples |
| 14 | Subnetting (Advanced) | VLSM, CIDR, practice 10+ problems |
| 15 | IPv6 + Comparison | IPv6 features, IPv4 vs IPv6 table |
| 16 | Routing: RIP + OSPF | Distance vector vs link state, algorithms |
| 17 | ARP + ICMP + NAT | How each works, interview questions |
| 18 | Fragmentation + Review | IP fragmentation, revise Network Layer |
| 19 | TCP Deep Dive | Header, 3-way handshake, 4-way termination |
| 20 | TCP Reliability + Flow Control | Sliding window, reliability mechanisms |
| 21 | TCP Congestion Control | Slow start, AIMD, fast retransmit/recovery, variants |
| 22 | UDP + TCP vs UDP | UDP mechanics, comparison table, use cases |
| 23 | HTTP + HTTPS + DNS | HTTP methods/codes, TLS, DNS resolution |
| 24 | DHCP + Email + FTP + SSH | DORA, SMTP/POP3/IMAP, FTP modes |
| 25 | Network Security | Encryption, TLS handshake, firewalls, VPN |
| 26 | Attacks + Authentication | Common attacks, defenses, auth methods |
| 27 | Modern Networking | CDN, load balancer, cloud networking |
| 28 | All Comparison Tables | TCP/UDP, IPv4/6, Hub/Switch/Router, etc. |
| 29 | Interview Questions | Practice beginner → advanced questions |
| 30 | Final Revision | Formulas, mnemonics, rapid-fire, mock interview |

