## 📝 Final Advice

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **The #1 interview question:** "What happens when you type google.com in your browser?"
> If you can answer this in 3-5 minutes covering DNS, TCP, TLS, HTTP, server processing, and rendering — **you've demonstrated strong networking knowledge.**

> [!TIP]
> **Study strategy that works:**
> 1. Read the concept
> 2. Close the book and explain it aloud (Feynman technique)
> 3. Solve 2-3 related problems
> 4. Write a short note from memory
> 5. Revisit after 1 day, 3 days, 7 days (spaced repetition)

> [!NOTE]
> **For product-based companies (Google, Amazon, Microsoft):**
> Focus on: TCP internals, congestion control, DNS, HTTP/2-3, CDN, load balancing, system design networking. They care about HOW and WHY, not just WHAT.

> [!NOTE]
> **For service-based companies (TCS, Infosys, Wipro):**
> Focus on: OSI model, TCP vs UDP, subnetting, basic protocols, port numbers, comparison tables. They test breadth more than depth.

